Although they've been working all summer, our staff is officially back today! We are excited to see students next week! Just a couple of important reminders:
- School starts Wednesday, August 26
- Start time is 8:00 am and end time is 3:20 pm.
- Parents, please take temps before your child goes to the bus. Bus drivers will be taking temps as well and we would like to ensure that a parent is present if a fever is detected.

post_text:
Kindergarten Screening

We will be holding Kindergarten Screening in the Elementary Cafeteria on August 14. Please bring your child to the front door. Their temperature will be taken upon entry. It will take about an hour to complete. Once completed, a teacher will go over the results of the screening with the parents. Parents may return to pick up their child or we will have a place for you to sit and wait. If you are unsure of what time your child's appointment is or you need to schedule for a screening, please call the elementary office Tuesday, August 11-Thursday, August 13 from 9:00 am - 3:00 pm.

post_text:
The following is a message from Kelly Heiskell at the Lamar Career and Technical Center:

Next week we will be allowing students to come to LCTC to pick up their belongings. We will also be asking them to return textbooks and other materials that belong to LCTC. Any unreturned books or items will result in billing to the student. Our pick up times will be as follows:
Tuesday 5/5: Noon-4pm
Wednesday 5/6: 8am-Noon

Students enrolled in Automotive, Welding, Machine Tool, or Carpentry should report to the outside shop bay door of their current program to collect their things. If students are enrolled in Graphic Design or Health Occupations they should report to the front entrance. Social distancing guidelines will be observed.

Instructors in Graphic Design and Health Occupations will be contacting students about completing certification tests. Automotive ASE testing will be conducted at LCTC on Wednesday, May 13th beginning at 10 am. These are the only programs still needing to complete certification assessments this academic year.
